      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While there is no verified scientific evidence that deception auto-generates specific sub-audible microtones or chest vibrations, stress and cognitive load when lying can physiologically alter a speaker's voice pitch, breath depth, and heart rate. These natural changes might create a subtle, discordant acoustic quality that your body subconsciously registered as a physical sensation, even if no such specific frequency was actually transmitted. It remains largely in the realm of anecdotal experience rather than established acoustics or biology.",
      "source": "target",
